{
  "texts": [
    "They proposed a fusion framework exploiting seven SSL models.",
    "For the OOD track, they applied semi-supervised learning to the unlabeled set, which was shown to be very effective.• The system from ByteDance AI-LAB (T20) [140] ranked 4th in terms of both system-and utterance-level SRCC.",
    "It was based on LDNet, and they combined the main and OOD track datasets with a shared encoder and separate decoders.",
    "The encoder was essentially a wav2vec 2.0 model fine-tuned for phoneme recognition.• MooseNet [141] was based on SSL-MOS, and their main idea was to apply PLDA.",
    "It transformed frame-by-frame acoustic features into time-invariant features by global pooling, an operation similar to that used to compute speaker vectors for speaker recognition tasks."
  ]
}